article.headline: E. Kentucky 59, Murray St. 58
article.story: MURRAY, Ky. (AP) -- Mike Rose hit a 3-pointer with 3.8 seconds left to lift Eastern Kentucky to a 59-58 win over Murray State on Wednesday night. Darnell Diallis led Eastern (4-4, 1-0 Ohio Valley Conference) with 20 points, and Adam Leonard scored 13 points. Bruce Carter paced Murray (3-3, 0-1) with 17 points. Eastern pulled within two points on a Leonard 3-pointer with 1:03 left. The Racers were still up by two points with 12 seconds left when Murray's Tyler Holloway was forced to put up an off-balance shot. Rose followed with his 3-pointer, and Murray couldn't recover. The Racers benefited early in the second half from nine points by Carter, giving Murray a 34-24 lead. Murray held on to the lead until Tony Easley drew a technical foul with eight minutes to go. Eastern then used a 7-2 run to pull within five. Eastern led by as much as seven points, 18-11 in the first half, but a Murray run gave the Racers a 25-24 lead at the half. The Colonels managed to score 11 points off nine Murray turnovers in the half.
